reviews.title: Quality food is disappointing
reviews.text: The last few times the food was very disappointing. The chicken chip joi had too much slimy sauce and much less vegetables than we are used to.

reviews.title: Removed
reviews.text: Picked up food there for the first time yesterday. Was really not tasty everything was sweet. Wasn't anything spicy on. Not for us anymore.

reviews.title: Recommended!
reviews.text:
Last night we (4 people) happened to arrive at this restaurant, after several times at other eateries in front of a closed door. Despite the fact that we sat down a bit late, we were kindly welcomed at Diamant Epe, a Chinese restaurant that still really looks like an 'old-fashioned' Chinese, in the positive sense of the word. We had a great meal here. The oriental tapas concept was a really nice way to get in touch with many new flavors. You could choose 3 dishes per person per round, and the menu offers plenty to choose from. Well-known and unknown dishes, grilled vegetables and meat, all kinds of sushi and vegetarian options, really nicely prepared. All four of us enjoyed ourselves and had more than enough, despite having to leave it at three rounds because of the time. There was even a whole dessert bar with ice cream and fruit that we just didn't get around to. The unspoiled drinking (at extra cost) is recommended and also gives plenty of options, from soda and juice to chocolate, coffee and tea. We had not been to this restaurant before, but after this positive experience we will definitely come back. 

Less reading

reviews.title: Poor service
reviews.text: In itself always to our liking but last night there was someone from the service who threw the plates on the table you looked angry and when we asked for waiter she came with yes instead of what can I do for you. Really rude and I reported this you get in response was busy she must have been tired absolutely no style next time I'll go somewhere else

reviews.title: Poor to moderate
reviews.text: For there to eat generally mediocre, quality food: too much rice with the sushi, salty or very bland, request for Wasabi must be made, card does not match given dishes moreover, card is poor to read, variation little, tablet works awkwardly, drinking took a while. For vegetarians and vegans not recommended. Takeaway used to be good, but now? Value for money perhaps almost reasonable, staff were good and friendly. But there is no second time.

tips.body: Een tips. Ik raad dit restaurant niet aan.

reviews.title: Recommended!
reviews.text:
Despite the fact that we live quite nearby, we had never eaten here.
Had dinner here on March 14th.
It looks quite neat.
Enough choice.
We went for a la carte because we are not big eaters.
We had spicy Thai chicken soup and tipan tenderloin with black pepper sauce and Chinese noodles and nasi.
The tipan could have sizzled a bit more but it was delicious and more than enough.
Quality/price ratio also okay.
Will definitely come back here!

reviews.title: Tasteless
reviews.text:
September 5 for the first pick up, bami, fou yonghai, pangang

Tasteless, same sauce for the dishes, no spice, nothing
Too bad 😥

If this is the standard, I wouldn't recommend this to anyone

reviews.title: Worth to try
reviews.text:
At the end of the Christmas holiday, we didn't want to cook and desided to go out for dinner. We had passed the restaurant multiple times and never tried. Situated between Heerde and Epe the restaurant does not stand out and it's easy to pass. 
This time we tried and  were pleasantly surprised.  The food is good. The staff is friendly  and they serve your food quickly after you've ordered. Plenty of choice for Oriental tapas, perhaps a little simple with dessert but the maindishes are really good. I think you should go.

reviews.title: Nice
reviews.text:
My family and I went for dinner and had a lovely meal. We ordered four different dishes and were served with plenty of food.
There were a lot of empty tables though and the restaurant seemed a bit cramped.

I’ve always loved train travel. There’s something special about settling into a window seat and watching the landscape drift past. And as a wheelchair user, that joy only grows when the journey feels easy: level boarding, space to move, and the kind of accessibility that lets you fully relax. For me, the best train rides—like weaving through the Tuscan countryside on Trenitalia—are never just a way to get from A to B; they're part of the adventure.
